Doc,<br><br>
Well put.  It has to stop somewhere.  A sword can cut both ways and two people have been known to die with simultaneous mortal thrusts.  The value of this is known only to the combatants, not the observers.  To what purpose?<br><br>
If Dick wants to take on Cook one on one then so be it.  I have no doubt Cook can fend for himself.  When you live your life on the firing line you learn to face your adversaries head on.  When they will not flush you rake the treeline.  Where did Dick go.  Snipers aren't favored by their target.  Cook is a M60 gunner.  Maximum rate of fire until a round finds its mark.  Just technique, nothing personal (my assumption only).<br><br>
If you remember we warned Richard when he fired the first volley.  He didn't listen,he should.  There is much to be gained.<br><br>
I am in total agreement with Cook.  The position of Richard and yourself are entirely different.  Right or wrong you had the conviction to stand for your values.  It matters little whether we agree or not.  If someone believes in something totally then I admire his personal integrity.  <br><br>
I myself question Richard.  There is no way people who believe as strongly as we do can avoid that issue.  We can listen, but can never respect.  He doesn't exhibit the integrity and persevervance that you did.  That should bother you.  He is not your equal so don't descend to his level.  He couldn't stand his ground.  That takes balls and you know it only too well.  You are doing it now.<br><br>
There have been many warriors over the centuries that had respect for each other, but still fought bloody battles.  We are arriving at that position.  You are earning the respect of these grizzled warriors.  Emotions are everyones enemy.  I guess it helps to have come from a world where emotions were a liability I could not afford.  It always created errors I could not recover.<br><br>
We.  I could accept a truce among us who are here now.  Richard must find his own ground to stand on.  He has not made the effort yet.  Respect is earned not offered.<br><br>

